724854f-a.text:
York Ave., (Ave. A), west side, from East 62nd to 64th Streets, as seen from clearance on the east side of York Ave. Shown are gas holders of the Consolidated Gas Co., and a major portion of the N.Y. Homoeopathic College, (Flower Hospital).
December 22, 1930.
P. L. Sperr.

York Avenue, west side, south from East 62nd Street, showing gas holders at this point. To the left is the Oueensboro Bridge paralleling 59th Street and from which point south,York Avenue alters its identity to Sutton Place.
October 9, 1935
tterenice Abbott, photo
